		<title>I Bet You Never Thought to Use a Form For That!</title>
		<link>https://wordpress.com/blog/2024/11/26/creative-ways-to-use-website-forms/</link>
					<comments>https://wordpress.com/blog/2024/11/26/creative-ways-to-use-website-forms/#respond</comments>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[WordPress.com Staff]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Tue, 26 Nov 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Tips and Tutorials]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://en.blog.wordpress.com/?p=72345</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[Go beyond contact forms with these six ideas.]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p>When you’re <a href="https://wordpress.com/website-builder/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">building a WordPress website</a>, there are some essential elements you likely want to include, such as a contact form. However, limiting your use of forms to your <a href="https://wordpress.com/go/website-building/how-to-build-a-business-contact-page-with-wordpress-blocks/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">contact page</a> is a missed opportunity to increase leads, boost engagement, and enhance the overall <a href="https://wordpress.com/go/website-building/website-structure-optimized-for-ux-seo/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">user experience (UX)</a> on your site.</p>



<p>There are many ways you can use forms on your WordPress site beyond providing visitors with a contact method. From collecting user feedback to generating leads and expanding your mailing list, forms offer dynamic and convenient ways to drive conversions.</p>



<p>In this post, we’ll start by discussing the role forms play in WordPress and how they can help you collect valuable information. Then we’ll introduce you to eight creative ways to use them on your site with some tips for making them effective.</p>



<p><strong><em>Note: We’ve saved the most surprising ways for the end, so keep reading!</em></strong></p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">An introduction to using forms on your WordPress site</h2>



<p>When most people think of website forms, they likely think of <a href="https://wordpress.com/go/website-building/how-to-create-an-effective-contact-page-for-your-website/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">contact forms</a>. These simple, embedded features let your visitors enter basic information to get in touch with you:</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img data-attachment-id="72349" data-permalink="https://wordpress.com/blog/2024/11/26/creative-ways-to-use-website-forms/contact-form-example-2/" data-orig-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/contact-form-example-2.jpg" data-orig-size="1400,926" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="contact-form-example-2" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/contact-form-example-2.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/contact-form-example-2.jpg?w=1024" loading="lazy" width="1400" height="926" src="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/contact-form-example-2.jpg" alt="an example of a contact form with a black background" class="wp-image-72349" srcset="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/contact-form-example-2.jpg 1400w, https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/contact-form-example-2.jpg?w=150&amp;h=99 150w, https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/contact-form-example-2.jpg?w=300&amp;h=198 300w, https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/contact-form-example-2.jpg?w=768&amp;h=508 768w, https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/contact-form-example-2.jpg?w=1024&amp;h=677 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px" /></figure>



<p>However, the use of online forms extends far beyond contact points. These documents allow you to easily and conveniently collect a wide variety of information from users and visitors directly from your website. You can also use them across other channels such as email and social media.</p>



<p>Website forms are beneficial because they provide straightforward ways of collecting lead-generating data that you can store and use in the future. Therefore, forms are essential tools to help you with marketing, sales, and promotions.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Another benefit of <a href="https://wordpress.com/go/digital-marketing/create-contact-form/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">using forms on your WordPress site</a> is that creating and embedding them is quick and easy.&nbsp;There are <a href="https://wordpress.com/go/website-building/the-12-best-wordpress-form-plugins-reviewed/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">several plugins</a> you can use to build forms if you require different functionality.&nbsp;<br><br>If you’re looking to create a standard form, you can also use the Form block on WordPress.com, which is powered by the <a href="https://jetpack.com/features/discussion/contact-forms/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Jetpack plugin</a> (<a href="https://wordpress.com/support/jetpack/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">which is included on every WordPress.com website</a>):</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img data-attachment-id="74872" data-permalink="https://wordpress.com/blog/2024/11/26/creative-ways-to-use-website-forms/jetpack-form-block-example/" data-orig-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/jetpack-form-block-example.png" data-orig-size="1634,812" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="jetpack-form-block-example" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/jetpack-form-block-example.png?w=300" data-large-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/jetpack-form-block-example.png?w=1024" loading="lazy" width="1024" height="508" src="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/jetpack-form-block-example.png?w=1024" alt="" class="wp-image-74872" srcset="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/jetpack-form-block-example.png?w=1022 1022w, https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/jetpack-form-block-example.png?w=150 150w, https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/jetpack-form-block-example.png?w=300 300w, https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/jetpack-form-block-example.png?w=768 768w, https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/jetpack-form-block-example.png 1634w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Six creative examples of forms you can create right now</h2>



<p>Now that we understand more about the role forms play in websites, let’s look at their different use cases. Below are six creative ways to use forms on your WordPress site, aside from your contact page.&nbsp;</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">1. Run fun contests and giveaways</h3>



<p><a href="https://wordpress.com/go/digital-marketing/how-and-why-to-launch-a-giveaway-on-your-website/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Running contests and giveaways</a> on your website is an excellent way to boost engagement. Giving away freebies can help promote your brand and spread awareness about specific products and offerings.&nbsp;</p>



<p>To make it as simple as possible for your customers to enter the contest, you can use an embedded or pop-up form to collect their information, such as names and email addresses:</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img data-attachment-id="74873" data-permalink="https://wordpress.com/blog/2024/11/26/creative-ways-to-use-website-forms/contest-form-example/" data-orig-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/contest-form-example.png" data-orig-size="768,580" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="contest-form-example" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/contest-form-example.png?w=300" data-large-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/contest-form-example.png?w=768" loading="lazy" width="768" height="580" src="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/contest-form-example.png?w=768" alt="" class="wp-image-74873" srcset="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/contest-form-example.png 768w, https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/contest-form-example.png?w=150 150w, https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/contest-form-example.png?w=300 300w" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px" /></figure>



<p>This form provides you with customer contact information that you can use for future campaigns. People will be more likely to hand over their details when they know they have a chance to win something in return.&nbsp;<br></p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">2. Register users for memberships and events</h3>



<p>If you run a <a href="https://wordpress.com/go/website-building/creating-a-membership-site-wordpress-com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">membership site</a> or host events, you can use website forms to make user registration a breeze:</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img data-attachment-id="74892" data-permalink="https://wordpress.com/blog/2024/11/26/creative-ways-to-use-website-forms/webinar-signup-form-example/" data-orig-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/webinar-signup-form-example.png" data-orig-size="2382,1348" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="webinar-signup-form-example" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/webinar-signup-form-example.png?w=300" data-large-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/webinar-signup-form-example.png?w=1024" loading="lazy" width="1024" height="579" src="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/webinar-signup-form-example.png?w=1024" alt="" class="wp-image-74892" srcset="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/webinar-signup-form-example.png?w=1024 1024w, https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/webinar-signup-form-example.png?w=2046 2046w, https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/webinar-signup-form-example.png?w=150 150w, https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/webinar-signup-form-example.png?w=300 300w, https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/webinar-signup-form-example.png?w=768 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Source: <a href="https://wpvip.com/event/newsrooms-redefining-digital-publishing-2025/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">WordPress VIP</a></figcaption></figure>



<p>You can also utilize them for event registration, such as an upcoming webinar. Like a giveaway, this can be an effective lead-generation technique because you’re giving users something in exchange for their contact details.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">3. Conduct user and reader surveys</h3>



<p>Curious to know what your readers or customers think about a topic? Use a questionnaire and find out! You can easily create a poll or survey using Crowdsignal, our service for creating surveys and polls. Get started with a <a href="https://crowdsignal.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">free account</a> and <a href="https://wordpress.com/support/forms/polls/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">learn how to set it up</a>:</p>



<figure class="wp-block-video wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-videopress"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title='VideoPress Video Player' aria-label='VideoPress Video Player' width='500' height='313' src='https://video.wordpress.com/embed/D2Dw1MBt?cover=1&amp;preloadContent=metadata&amp;useAverageColor=1&amp;hd=0' frameborder='0' allowfullscreen data-resize-to-parent="true"  allow='clipboard-write' ></iframe><script src='https://v0.wordpress.com/js/next/videopress-iframe.js?m=1725245713'></script>
</div><figcaption>Source: <a href="https://crowdsignal.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Crowdsignal</a></figcaption></figure>



<p>You can also effortlessly capture insights from your audience by creating a simple poll using the <a href="https://wordpress.com/support/wordpress-editor/blocks/poll-block/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Poll block</a>:</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img data-attachment-id="74879" data-permalink="https://wordpress.com/blog/2024/11/26/creative-ways-to-use-website-forms/poll-form-example/" data-orig-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/poll-form-example.png" data-orig-size="809,435" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="poll-form-example" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/poll-form-example.png?w=300" data-large-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/poll-form-example.png?w=809" loading="lazy" width="809" height="435" src="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/poll-form-example.png?w=809" alt="" class="wp-image-74879" srcset="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/poll-form-example.png 809w, https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/poll-form-example.png?w=150 150w, https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/poll-form-example.png?w=300 300w, https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/poll-form-example.png?w=768 768w" sizes="(max-width: 809px) 100vw, 809px" /></figure>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">4. Let users sign up for your mailing list</h3>



<p><a href="https://wordpress.com/go/digital-marketing/your-email-newsletter-strategy-5-key-components-of-success/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Email marketing</a> is a powerful way to grow your audience, expand brand awareness, and increase engagement. However, figuring out how to grow your subscriber list can be challenging.</p>



<p>One way to expand your subscriber list is by embedding a newsletter signup form on your website. It lets you easily capture the email addresses of your visitors:</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img data-attachment-id="74877" data-permalink="https://wordpress.com/blog/2024/11/26/creative-ways-to-use-website-forms/subscription-form-example/" data-orig-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/subscription-form-example.png" data-orig-size="2392,406" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="subscription-form-example" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/subscription-form-example.png?w=300" data-large-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/subscription-form-example.png?w=1024" loading="lazy" width="1024" height="173" src="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/subscription-form-example.png?w=1024" alt="" class="wp-image-74877" srcset="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/subscription-form-example.png?w=1024 1024w, https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/subscription-form-example.png?w=1019 1019w, https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/subscription-form-example.png?w=2039 2039w, https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/subscription-form-example.png?w=150 150w, https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/subscription-form-example.png?w=300 300w, https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/subscription-form-example.png?w=768 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>One of the benefits of signup forms is that there are so many different areas you can place them. For example, you can insert them in the header or footer of your website. This placement ensures the forms are easily accessible no matter which pages your users are on.&nbsp;</p>



<p>You can also use forms as exit-intent pop-ups. For example, as visitors are about to leave your website, you can have the signup form appear with a convenient Call To Action (CTA).</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">5. Enable applicants to apply for jobs</h3>



<p>Recruiting and <a href="https://wordpress.com/go/website-building/how-to-attract-top-talent-with-your-websites-careers-page/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">hiring new talent</a> is a staple in any successful business. However, the application process you use can influence the number of applicants and the quality.</p>



<p>Today, many job seekers want a quick and convenient way to apply to jobs they’re interested in. To make the process as convenient as possible for your prospects, you can add a form on your website that enables potential employees to apply to open positions:</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img data-attachment-id="74897" data-permalink="https://wordpress.com/blog/2024/11/26/creative-ways-to-use-website-forms/image-134/" data-orig-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/image-2.png" data-orig-size="768,649" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="image" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/image-2.png?w=300" data-large-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/image-2.png?w=768" loading="lazy" width="768" height="649" src="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/image-2.png?w=768" alt="" class="wp-image-74897" srcset="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/image-2.png 768w, https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/image-2.png?w=150 150w, https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/image-2.png?w=300 300w" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px" /></figure>



<p>You can embed these forms directly below the job descriptions. Plus, you can enable applicants to attach documents, such as resumes and cover letters. This feature eliminates the number of steps users must complete to submit their information for different positions.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Using a form also helps you keep all the necessary information of applicants in one place for easy access. This can streamline the vetting process and, ultimately, help you find the most qualified applicants.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">6. “Name It!” campaign – involve users in product decisions</h3>



<p>Raise your hand if you’ve ever eagerly suggested a name for someone’s new puppy, or your local zoo’s newborn giraffe. Users love feeling useful, so give them a fun job. Create a form that allows visitors to suggest a name for your latest product or mascot. An entire viral campaign can sometimes emerge simply from a “name this” campaign.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img data-attachment-id="74882" data-permalink="https://wordpress.com/blog/2024/11/26/creative-ways-to-use-website-forms/name-it-campaign-example/" data-orig-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/name-it-campaign-example.png" data-orig-size="1414,1438" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="name-it-campaign-example" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/name-it-campaign-example.png?w=295" data-large-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/name-it-campaign-example.png?w=1007" loading="lazy" width="1007" height="1024" src="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/name-it-campaign-example.png?w=1007" alt="" class="wp-image-74882" srcset="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/name-it-campaign-example.png?w=1007 1007w, https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/name-it-campaign-example.png?w=147 147w, https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/name-it-campaign-example.png?w=295 295w, https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/name-it-campaign-example.png?w=768 768w, https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2024/11/name-it-campaign-example.png 1414w" sizes="(max-width: 1007px) 100vw, 1007px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Be forewarned that if you let your audience name something, the results might get a little bit silly. Source: <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-36225652" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">BBC</a></figcaption></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">A few simple tips for creating effective website forms</h2>



<p>Once you decide to create a particular type of website form, the next step is to build it. As we mentioned earlier, there are various tools you can use to do so.&nbsp;</p>



<p>However, regardless of which plugin you use to create your forms, there are some essential tips to keep in mind to ensure effectiveness. For example:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Keep things simple</strong>. Only include the necessary information to keep the forms as brief and concise as possible. Otherwise, you risk overwhelming users and reducing the likelihood of completing the form.</li>



<li><strong>Minimize the amount of typing involved</strong>. In most cases, your customers won’t want to spend considerable time filling out lengthy responses to form questions. Therefore, it’s a smart idea to include multiple choice answers when possible (and where applicable).</li>



<li><strong>Provide clear instructions</strong>. To make your forms as effective as possible, it’s vital to ensure that users understand what you’re asking and how to complete the fields correctly. You might consider adding example answers to demonstrate the type of responses you’re looking for.</li>
</ul>



<p>Best practices for creating website forms vary based on the type you’re building and what your end goal is. However, it’s crucial to prioritize the UX to make the data collection process quick and effortless for your customers.&nbsp;</p>



<h1 class="wp-block-heading">What will you do with forms next?</h1>



<p>Most website owners understand the importance of including contact forms on their websites. However, many overlook the various ways that forms can help drive conversions and generate leads.</p>



<p>As discussed in this post, you can use plenty of strategies to get creative with your forms. For example, you can use them to register users for events, conduct user surveys, let visitors sign up for your mailing list, and offer a seamless way to apply for jobs.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Ready to build a site of your own? <a href="http://wordpress.com/website-builder/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Get started with WordPress.com now</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
